[{"_path":"/legacy-articles/2021-06-18-after-reading-remote-work-of-mungkeii","_dir":"legacy-articles","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"en","_empty":false,"title":"讀五十六巷七弄的〈淺談 Remote work〉有感","description":"","excerpt":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h1","props":{"id":"前言"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"前言"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"這篇文章是我去年三月底，發布在公司內部 "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"#cop-wfh"}]},{"type":"text","value":" 頻道的訊息，那是一個討論如何適應 WFH 工作模式的頻道。我把它簡單重整為文章的斷句方式後，放到部落格作個紀錄。"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h1","props":{"id":"本文"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"本文"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"分享 "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://medium.com/@jacquetwong?source=post_page-----63e75a8f1213--------------------------------","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jac Wong"}]},{"type":"text","value":" 在 Medium 所寫的"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://medium.com/%E4%BA%94%E5%8D%81%E5%85%AD%E5%B7%B7%E4%B8%83%E5%BC%84/%E6%B7%BA%E8%AB%87-remote-work-63e75a8f1213","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"〈淺談 Remote work〉"}]},{"type":"text","value":"這篇文章。"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"特別想 mention 是裡面提到的「溝通文化」，和我之前想表達的概念相近，但有幾個不錯的術語，我覺得是可以借用的。我嘗試用我的理解與言語再論述一次看看。"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"blockquote","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"通常大家只記得好處，卻忘了 remote work 對團隊工作的影響。衝擊最大的，莫過於從 synchronous、under-communication 走向 asynchronous、over-communication。"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"因為 Remote 會導致 Face to Face 的成本變高，而基於公司的 WFH 政策，我們現在也只能 Remote Call，甚至更多是連視訊都沒開的 Call，其效益會比 Face to Face 低很多。又因為 Face to Face & Remote Call 這類的同步溝通方式，一次只能進行一個話題，很容易 Lock 一群人的 conversation，變得互相在等待。"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"而通常為了降低被 Lock 住的時間，所以說話會盡量精簡、不囉唆，也就是文中所述的 under-communication。（事實上，平時我們面對面溝通，使用 under-communication 時，更多是可以透過語氣、肢體語言、表情去將省略的資訊補齊。）但因為 WFH 在溝通上，Remote Call (or Discord/Zoom)，更容易有 Lock 的情況，且每個人家裡網路情況不一、容易有不穩、或掉訊的狀況。"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"一直透過 Remote Call 進行同步溝通，不一定是有效率的方式。所以為了減少等待的浪費，非同步 (asynchronous) 溝通就變得很重要。"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"而 async 溝通時，不會像同步溝通時，預期所有人都會同時接到訊息，所以一個訊息或內容，我們預期會在將來被多人多次使用。因此為了將來的訊息接受者（包括未來的自己）能夠看懂，我們必須將只適用於處於當下情境者的 mutual knowledge，變成任何人看了都能夠暸解的 common knowledge。而要維持 common knowledge，就仰賴資訊量比較多、比較細、感覺上比較囉唆的的 over communicate。在實踐上可能包括："}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"將正式會議的記錄寫在 Confluence 上"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"把非正式會議、討論、對話的結論打在 Slack 上"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"在決議的資訊上，除了結果外，也盡量把決策的原因、考量寫下來"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"在文字對談上，盡量把脈絡講明"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"有更多想法的也可以一起交流"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"blockquote","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"在擁抱 remote work 的同時，卻不擁抱 async overcommunication 的文化，就會出事。"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n因為當一個人 remote work 時，和他合作的人也自動被 remote 了。"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n那就是整個團隊的事。"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"我滿喜歡這段話的，所以特地摘錄分享之。"}]}]},"title_en":"After Reading \"Remote Work\" of @mungkeii","slug":"after-reading-remote-work-of-mungkeii","aliases":["讀五十六巷七弄的〈淺談 Remote work〉有感","Aft